e players each try to score by shooting a ball through the opponent's hoop. Founded by James Naismith in 1891, the NBA showcases the world's elite talent.", "Baseball is a bat-and-ball sport played between two teams of nine players on a diamond-shaped field. Known as America's pastime, the World Series is the championship of Major League Baseball in the United States and Canada."], "scores": [0.6599860518777645, 0.5974166068435075, 0.555794934929573, 0.5288441043217444, 0.5253647785996965], "model_name": "mpnet", "document_ids": ["Soccer", "Cricket", "Rugby", "Basketball", "Baseball"]}}